    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-07-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="262"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d262">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Neill</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Blaine</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Lima, Peru</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-07-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 27, 1892</hi>
                        </date>. (Received August 22.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 407.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that as the regular
                    session of Congress opens to-morrow (the 28th instant), I have placed a note in
                    the hands of his excellency Señor Larrabrue y Unanne, minister of foreign <pb
                        facs="0317" n="1051" xml:id="pg_1051"/> relations here, in reference to the
                    long-pending claim of citizens of the United States, upon the Government of
                    Peru, known as the Hydro-graphic Commission of the Amazon, as per my inclosed
                    communication.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard R. Neill.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No. 407.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Neill</persName> to Señor
                                <persName type="to">Larrabrue</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Lima</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-07-27">
                                <hi rend="italic">July 27, 1892</hi>.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Minister</hi>: I would respectfully call the
                        attention of your excellency to the various notes from this legation as to
                        the character of the claim known as the Hydro-graphic Commission of the
                        Amazon.</p>
                    <p>I would earnestly request your excellency to have this claim again presented
                        before the honorable Congress of Peru during the present session for its
                        early consideration.</p>
                    <p>I express the hope that some action will soon be taken to facilitate the
                        early and final settlement of this long-pending claim of citizens of the
                        United States upon the Government of Peru.</p>
                    <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard R. Neill.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
